definition: few/less/to lack/to be missing/to stop (doing sth)/seldom

sentences.english: I went to arrest Goebbels, taking a Leutnant and a squad of men with me.
sentences.chinese: 我帶着少尉和一小隊人去逮捕戈培爾。

sentences.english: Lieutenant Hearn fingered the magazine on his carbine.
sentences.chinese: 候恩少尉用手摸了一下卡賓槍的彈盒。

sentences.english: Can't have ensigns assigned to the Sentinels;
sentences.chinese: 我們不能把只有少尉軍銜的人派到哨兵這裏來。

sentences.english: The Lieutenant Commander wanted to get into the fight.
sentences.chinese: 少尉想去和聖約人戰鬥。

sentences.english: He found in India that subalterns were two a penny and invited nowhere.
sentences.chinese: 和少尉軍官多得不值錢，在哪兒也不會成爲座上客。

sentences.english: They silently removed the ensign pips from each other's epaulets, and fastened the jg bars there.
sentences.chinese: 他倆默默的取下對方的少尉肩章，換上中尉的標識。

sentences.english: Ok, then. Report back to me or to Lt. Mumphreys when you have.
sentences.chinese: 好，那麼，當你完成了就來向我或者馬姆利少尉報告。

sentences.english: Lt. Nixon thinks this is a can of peaches.
sentences.chinese: 尼克森少尉認爲這是一罐桃子。

sentences.english: Lieutenant Winters, I want canteens out of belts with the caps unscrewed.
sentences.chinese: 溫特斯少尉，命令他們把水壺取下來，打開蓋子。

sentences.english: At 16, napoleon received a commission as a second lieutenant of artillery .
sentences.chinese: 16歲的拿破崙得到了炮兵少尉的任命狀。

sentences.english: His plan was to become a Marine Corps second lieutenant.
sentences.chinese: 他計劃參加海軍陸戰隊，成爲一名少尉。

sentences.english: 18Second Lieutenant Andrew Ferrara, with the 27th Infantry Regiment, packs Gobstopper candy with the rest of his arsenal
sentences.chinese: 第27步兵團少尉安德魯費拉拉兜裏還塞有硬糖。

sentences.english: Among them were sixteen colonels and 282 officers of the rank of lieutenant or above.
sentences.chinese: 其中有十六名上校和二百八十二名少尉以上的軍官。

sentences.english: The last German soldier to die was Leutnant Tomas.
sentences.chinese: 德軍最後一個被殺的是托馬斯少尉。

sentences.english: Surely you didn't think you could evade the Reich for long, Lieutenant?
sentences.chinese: 我想你應該想說可以躲避的了高射炮火力吧，少尉？

definition: junior ranking officer in Chinese army/major/lieutenant commander
middle ranking officer in Chinese army/lieutenant colonel/commander
high ranking officer in Chinese army/colonel
lowest-ranked noncommissioned officer (e.g. corporal in the army or petty officer, third class in the navy)
senior official/senior officer/commanding officer/CL:位[wei4]/sir (term of address for senior officer)
